timeline.bodyText:
Couldn't this just be something like:
public class OpenMRSNarrativeTemplateManifest extends ca.uhn.fhir.narrative2.NarrativeTemplateManifest {
	public static NarrativeTemplateManifest forManifestFileLocation(String... propertyFiles) throws IOException {
		return forManifestFileLocation(Arrays.asList(propertyFiles));
	}

	public static NarrativeTemplateManifest forManifestFileLocation(Collection<String> propertyFiles) throws IOException {
		log.debug("Loading narrative properties file(s): {}", propertyFiles);
		return new NarrativeTemplateManifest(propertyFiles.stream().map(r -> loadResource(r)).map(p -> NarrativeTemplateManifest.loadProperties(p))
			.flatMap(p -> p.stream()).map(t -> new OpenmrsNarrativeTemplate(t)).collect(Collectors.toList()));
	}

	static String loadResource(String name) throws IOException {
		if (name.startsWith("openmrs:")) {
			File file = new File(OpenmrsUtil.getApplicationDataDirectory(), name.substring("openmrs:".length()));

			if (file.exists() == false) {
				throw new IOException("File not found: " + file.getAbsolutePath());
			}

			try (FileInputStream inputStream = new FileInputStream(file)) {
				return IOUtils.toString(inputStream, Charsets.UTF_8);
			}
		} else {
			return NarrativeTemplateManifest.loadResource(name);
		}
	}
}
(The above adds a small dependency that we create a constructor for OpenmrsNarrativeTemplate that takes a NarrativeTemplate, but that isn't too hard. That way we cut the code down to what we minimally need to support this change.

